{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.evalGround\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">Simp</span>.<span class=\"name\">evalGround</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">config</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.EvalStepConfig\">EvalStepConfig</a> := <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.EvalStepConfig.mk\">{</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.EvalStepConfig.mk\">}</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/SimpM.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.Simproc\">Simproc</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Simplification procedure that evaluates ground terms of builtin types.\n\n**Important:** This procedure assumes subterms have already been simplified. It evaluates\na single operation on literal arguments only. For example:\n- `2 + 3` → evaluates to `5`\n- `2 + (3 * 4)` → returns `.rfl` (the argument `3 * 4` is not a literal)\n\nThe simplifier is responsible for term traversal, ensuring subterms are reduced\nbefore `evalGround` is called on the parent expression.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.evalGround","kind":"def","line":602,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.evalGround","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.lean#L602-L656"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.EvalStepConfig.maxExponent\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">Simp</span>.<span class=\"name\">EvalStepConfig</span>.<span class=\"name\">maxExponent</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.EvalStepConfig\">EvalStepConfig</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.EvalStepConfig.maxExponent","kind":"def","line":600,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.EvalStepConfig.maxExponent","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.lean#L600-L600"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.EvalStepConfig.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sym</span>.<span class=\"name\">Simp</span>.<span class=\"name\">EvalStepConfig</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.EvalStepConfig\">Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.EvalStepConfig</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.EvalStepConfig.mk","kind":"ctor","line":599,"name":"Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.EvalStepConfig.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Sym/Simp/EvalGround.lean#L599-L600"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sy